---
title: One-Pan Chicken Alfredo with Parmesan, Fresh Oregano, and Broccoli
description: If you’re like us, your mouth starts watering at the mere mention of spaghetti alfredo, and your mind races with visions of creamy sauce and noodles wrapped just so around the prongs of your fork. But what if we told you that our version also can be made with only one pan (read: SUPER easy cleanup)? If that doesn’t make you exclaim “sign me up,” we don’t know what will.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/one-pan-chicken-alfredo-dba85e53.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/one-pan-chicken-alfredo-c81528e0.pdf
course: main course
time required: 50 minutes
cuisine: North America
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pan-chicken-alfredo-59033052c6243b049f065022
author: Michelle Doll Olson
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 800 kcal
  fat: 27 g
  saturated fat: 12 g
  carbohydrates: 80 g
  sugar: 8 g
  protein: 62 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 540 mg
---

Wash and dry all produce. Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Pick
@oregano{1/4%cup}(leaves picked and stems discarded) leaves from stems; discard
stems. Finely chop leaves. Finely chop @parsley{1/2%cup}(finely chopped).
Thinly slice @chicken breasts{2}(thinly sliced into bite-sized strips) and
season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tbsp} in a #large pan{} or #pot over
medium-high heat. Add @broccoli florets{16} and cook, tossing, until bright
green and tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Remove
from pan and set aside.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if you're having trouble getting broccoli to cook.

Heat another large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tbsp} in same #pan over
medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook, tossing occasionally, until browned all
over, ~{4-6%minutes}. Remove from pan and set aside with broccoli.

Melt @butter{2%tbsp} in same #pan over low heat. Add garlic and cook until
fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}. Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{2}, a large
pinch of salt, and @water{5%cups}, scraping up any brown bits on bottom, then
add @milk{1%cup} and @spaghetti{12%oz}. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a
simmer. Cook, stirring occasionally, until spaghetti is al dente and sauce is
creamy, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Add broccoli, chicken, oregano, half the parsley, half the
@parmesan cheese{1/2%cup}(grated), and @butter{2%tbsp} to pan. Cook, tossing,
until everything is warmed through, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Divide pasta between #bowls{}. Garnish with remaining parsley and Parmesan and
serve.